> (It would know where to expect an identifier and where to expect an expression etc.)<p>But that doesn&#x27;t mean that what&#x27;s in the macro should be highlighted like Rust:<p><pre><code>    sql!(&quot;SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = $1&quot;);
</code></pre>
is a macro provided by <a href="https://github.com/sfackler/rust-postgres-macros" rel="nofollow">https://github.com/sfackler/rust-postgres-macros</a> , and should be highlighted like SQL, not like a Rust string.<p><pre><code>    sql!(&quot;SELECT * FORM users WHERE name = $1&quot;);
</code></pre>
throws an error, because it&#x27;s malformed.
